This folder contains all files necessary to setup Jenkins build server for MrChecker source.

docker-compose.yaml is an entry file. It defines Jenkins master, 2 build agents and SeleniumGrid for testing purpose.
Jenkins component uses local docker image of Jenkins. If not existent, it's built using dockerfile in the folder.

To start Jenkins execute "docker-compose up".
Jenkins runs on port: 8888.

If first-time start & configuration: 
- conosle log contains access token to Jenkins
- an admin user must be created
- Seed.groovy file contains code to create all pipelines. To use it create a new pipeline "SetMeUp" and use the code from the script in NON sandbox mode.
Run the job. Jenkins will complain about missing script approvals. Make approvals to proceed. 
- Jenkins stores its data in ./jenkins folder

